If you were in lower Manhattan and looking for good lunch, Nish Nush would be a perfect choice! I went there one week ago, and that was my first visit. The cashier was nice, cause she helped me a lot to understand their menu. The food was legit to try. The salad with yogurt sauce was tasty and hummus was savory. The best thing was falafels. It was crispy on the outside, soft on the inside. The combination of falafels and hummus was like peanut butter and jelly. The icing on the cake is you can eat this delicious cuisine only with $13 to $15. And you don't need to tip them cause you serve your food by yourself. The only reason I didn't give the perfect score on this restaurant is a lack of various tastes. We ordered three different dishes but each dish was almost same. Beside that, all of my friends and I were satisfied with this nice, friendly, and exotic place.

I too like the previous reviewer had a negative experience with this place in the same week. The food is good, but I was not feeling how I was upcharged for replacing falafel for cauliflower. The upcharge is supposed to be for additionals, not replacements, and cauliflower is not some supreme upgrade. I have food sensitivities to peas, so go ahead and take advantage of my health conditions.  Update: The manager responded saying upcharging for a swap is common practice. Understandable if I was asking for steak, but I asked for freaking cauliflower vs. the falafel. They responded with $10 to the restaurant, but the manager's response lacks empathy for people with food allergens or sensitivities. Plenty of restaurants in the neighborhood will do a swap as long as its in reason (i.e. Fields Good Chicken which is a block away). She claimed it's because they had to "add ingredients" to do this swap. The falafels and cauliflower are already pre-cooked/prepped and are of lesser value as a vegetable. You didn't have to add anything. And what you replaced it with was not a steak, vegan cheese, almond milk, or anything premium.  Don't go here if you're allergic to any ingredients and need to swap those allergens out. They'll take it as an opportunity to charge you for something biologically not your fault.  P.S. Taim on the next block does an equally good job with their Falafel and their cauliflower salad is $3 less.
